''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|41.8% ''1,850''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|6.4% ''282''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[1900 United States presidential election|1900]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''49.1%''' ''2,301''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|49.1% ''2,299''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|1.8% ''85''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[1896 United States presidential election|1896]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|47.7% ''2,172''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''51.4%''' ''2,342''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|0.9% ''43''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[1892 United States presidential election|1892]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|45.4% ''1,790''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''47.6%''' ''1,875''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|7.0% ''274''\n|}\n{{Hidden end}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[National Register of Historic Places listings in Crawford County, Illinois]]\n\n==Sources==\n* Perrin, William Henry, ed.. ''History of Crawford and Clark Counties, Illinois'' Chicago, Illinois. O. L. Baskin & Co. (1883).\n\n==References==\n;Specific\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n;General\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070310144543/http://www.cyberdriveillinois.com/departments/archives/irad/edgar.html United States Census Bureau 2007 TIGER/Line Shapefiles]\n* [http://geonames.usgs.gov/domestic/ United States Board on Geographic Names (GNIS)]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081205020547/http://www.nationalatlas.gov/ United States National Atlas]\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.genealogytrails.com/ill/crawford/index.html Crawford County, Illinois History and Genea