tions]]\n|-\n|Are You Cinderella (Short)\n|Composer\n|Charles Hall\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1999\n|[[Third Watch]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n|[[Providence (American TV series)|Providence]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1997\n|Daisy Feldman's New York (Short)\n|Composer\n|Amy Geltman\n|-\n|Prix Fixe (Short)\n|Composer\n|Other Pictures\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1996\n|[[Intimate Portrait]]: [[Doris Duke]]\n|Composer\n|[[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]]\n|-\n|The O.J. Simpson Trial: Beyond Black & White\n|Composer\n|[[ABC Television Network|ABC]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |1995\n|[[Intimate Portrait]]: [[Katherine Hepburn]]\n|Composer\n|[[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |1995 - 1999\n|[[Biography (TV program)]] (19 Episodes)\n|Composer\n|[[A&E (TV channel)]]\n|-}\n\n==References==\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Egloff, Georg Brandl}}\n[[Category:American male composers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American composers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Film composer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Georg Brandl Egloff\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Georg Brandl Egloff\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1963|2|16|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Monterey]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation           = Producer, Composer \n| years_active         = 1994\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Laura Shanahan|1999|2014|end=died}}\n| children           = 2\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist | embed=yes\n| background           = solo_singer\n| genre                = {{flatlist|\n* [[Film score|Film music]]\n* [[Theme music]]\n* TV Scores\n* Commercial Scores\n}}\n| instrument           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Piano]]\n* [[Keyboard instrument|Keyboards]]\n}}\n| associated_acts      = \n| website              = \n}}\n}}\n\n'''Georg Brandl Egloff''' is an American producer and composer of music for film, television, radio, and commercials.  He has composed music for ''[[Shameless (American TV series)|Shameless]]'', ''[[The Goldbergs (2013 TV series)|The Goldbergs]]'', ''[[The West Wing]]'', and ''[[A&E Biography]]'', among others, as well as writing the Station ID music for the ''[[Hallmark Channel]]''.  He wrote the main theme music for ''[[This I Believe]]'' series on ''[[All Things Considered]]'' and ''[[Morning Edition]]'', and composes and produces music for ''[[Milk Street Radio]]'' and ''[[America's Test Kitchen]]'' (PBS and NPR).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R13OAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA254&lpg=PA254&dq=georg+brandl+egloff+music&source=bl&ots=yfnTfIq8lA&sig=ACfU3U1KYByNyIrLYDI9cbEQyZy5AHoNow&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwihx_meg4XoAhXEi54KHYdzD0g4ChDoATAJegQIChAB#v=onepage&q=georg%20brandl%20eglof%20music&f=false|title=This I Believe II: More Personal Philosophies of Remarkable Men and Women by Jay Allison and Dan Gediman |publisher=Henry Holt & Company |date=2008 |accessdate=March 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.177milkstreet.com/radio/cast|title=Christopher Kimball's Milk Street Radio Cast |publisher=Milk Street Radio |date= |accessdate=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early Life==\nGeorg Brandl Egloff was born in [[Monterey, California]] to parents, David and Susan Egloff. He grew up in Oberlin, Ohio. He attended the Berklee College of Music in Boston and received a Bachelor's degree in performance and composition in 1986.  That same year, he moved to [[New York City]] where he performed as a jazz pianist in Manhattan. Egloff served as the Tuesday night house pianist at the famous [[Village Gate]] club on [[Bleecker Street]]. \n\nDuring that period, he performed at [[The Village Vanguard]], [[Blue Note Jazz Club|The Blue Note]], Chicago Blues, Zanzibar, [[The Knitting Factory]], [[Sweet Basil]] and many others. Georg worked with many jazz and blues instrumentalists and singers including Blues greats [[Ruth Brown]] and [[Linda Hopkins]].  For most of the 90's, he used his first and middle names only.  Georg Brandl.\n\n==Music Career==\nIn the 1990s, Egloff began working in rock and pop music venues with singers including [[Jeff Buckley]], [[Joan Osborne]], [[Ronnie Spector]] and [[Johnny Thunders]]. He recorded as a session keyboardist for record producers [[Phil Ramone]] and [[Frank Filipetti]] and recorded a version of \"[[My Way (song)|My Way]]\" for the [[Frank Sinatra]] [[Duets (Frank Sinatra album)|''Duets'' series]].\n\n==Film and Television Music==\nIn 1994, producers at ABC News Productions contacted Egloff to write music for a biography of [[Hillary Clinton]], followed by more than a dozen A&E Biographies and started a string jobs composing music for film and television programs. \n\nHe has written for ''[[The West Wing]]'', ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'', ''[[Pan Am (TV series)|Pan Am]]'', ''[[Third Watch]]'', ''[[Shameless (U.S. TV series)|Shameless]],'' and various programs airing on [[HBO]],  [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]], and [[Lifetime Television]]. His film work includes ''[[The Company Men]]'', ''The Big Time (2002 film)|The Big Time'', ''[[The Babymakers]]'', ''[[The Terminal]]'', ''[[Little Monsters]]'', ''Just One Year'', and ''Lucky''.\n\nEgloff performed on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' as a solo pianist on numerous occasions, including a Christmas performance with [[Kermit the Frog]] and a 2 hour Halloween special with movie director [[Wes Craven]]. For 4 years he was keyboardist for Charlie's Dilemma, a band led by singer/songwriter Charlie Mangold.  For a number of years, Egloff wrote, arranged, and recorded music for the Fashion and Fragrance Awards held at [[Radio City Music Hall]] and Lincoln Center's [[Avery Fisher Hall]].\n\n===Filmography===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Production \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n|[[The Magicians (American TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Syfy]]\n|-\n|[[Wayne (TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[YouTube Premium]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2018\n|[[American Woman (TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Paramount Network]]\n|-\n|[[Super Troopers 2]]\n|Composer, Arranger\n|[[Fox Searchlight Pictures]]\n|-\n|[[Shameless (American TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2016\n|[[The Goldbergs (season 4)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n|-\n|[[Shameless (American TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n|-\n|Spirit Lake Cycles\n|Composer\n|Documentary\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2014\n|[[Shameless (American TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2013\n|[[Under the Dome (TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[CBS]]\n|-\n|BlacK Kat\n|Composer\n|Documentary\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2012\n|[[The Babymakers]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Blumhouse Productions]]\n|-\n|[[Shameless (American TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n|-\n|Little Monsters\n|Composer\n|VCI Entertainment\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2011\n|[[Pan Am (TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n|-\n|[[The Lying Game (TV series)]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Warner Horizon Television]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2010\n|[[The Company Men]] \n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2009\n|[[Southland (TV series)]] \n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n|[[ER (TV series)]]\n|Music Producer, Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Warner Bros. Television]]\n|-\n|Spooner\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|Super Crispy Entertainment\n|-\n|All Ages Night\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|Freedom Girl Productions\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2008\n|[[Cold Case (season 4)]] \n|Composer\n|[[CBS]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2006\n|[[Studio 60 on the Sunset Strip]] \n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Warner Brothers Television]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2003\n|[[The West Wing]]\n|Actor, Musician (duet with [[James Taylor]])\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n|[[The West Wing]]\n|Additional Composer\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2002\n|The Big Time \n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[TNT]]\n|-\n|Studio Bob (TV series)\n|Composer\n|[[Brian Cox (director)]]\n|-\n|Over My Dead Body (Short)\n|Composer\n|[[Arie Posin]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2001\n|[[The Jimmy Show]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt0271020/credits/?ref_=bo_tt_tab|title=The Jimmy Show|publisher=Box Office Mojo |date= |accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref> \n|Composer, Additional Music\n|Next Wednesday Productions\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2000\n|[[Citizen Baines]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Warner Brothers Television]]\n|-\n|Prince of Central Park\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[Lorimar Productions]]\n|-\n|Are You Cinderella (Short)\n|Composer\n|Charles Hall\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1999\n|[[Third Watch]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n|[[Providence (American TV series)|Providence]]\n|Composer, Additional Music\n|[[NBC]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1997\n|Daisy Feldman's New York (Short)\n|Composer\n|Amy Geltman\n|-\n|Prix Fixe (Short)\n|Composer\n|Other Pictures\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1996\n|[[Intimate Portrait]]: [[Doris Duke]]\n|Composer\n|[[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]]\n|-\n|The O.J. Simpson Trial: Beyond Black & White\n|Composer\n|[[ABC Television Network|ABC]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |1995\n|[[Intimate Portrait]]: [[Katherine Hepburn]]\n|Composer\n|[[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |1995 - 1999\n|[[Biography (TV program)]] (19 Episodes)\n|Composer\n|[[A&E (TV channel)]]\n|-}\n\n==References==\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Egloff, Georg Brandl}}\n[[Category:American male composers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American composers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male musicians]]\n", "name_user": "Pennyframstad", "label"