7PZfUegA&hl=en&ppis=_e&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiov5TMpOvnAhWhknIEHcTaDQUQ6AEwD3oECAwQAQ#v=onepage&q=Pratt%20Graphic%20Art%20Center%20logo&f=false |language=en}}</ref> The Pratt Graphic Art Center closed in 1986.<ref name=\"City Guide\">{{cite web |title=Pratt Institute Launches New Printmaking Program |url=https://www.cityguideny.com/event/Pratt-Institute-2019-08-28-2019-08-28 |website=City Guide |accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Manhattan Graphics Center\">{{cite web |title=Mission and History |url=https://www.manhattangraphicscenter.org/mission-and-history |website=Manhattan Graphics Center |accessdate=22 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe [[National Gallery of Art]] in Washington, DC has collected prints published by the Pratt Graphic Art Center.<ref name=\"National Gallery of Art\">{{cite web |title=Pratt Graphic Art Center |url=https://www.nga.gov/collection/artist-info.35026.html |website=National Gallery of Art |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> Artists represented in this collection include\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Al Blaustein]]\n*[[Luis Camnitzer]]\n*Albert Christ-Janer\n*Roberto De Lamonica\n*[[Arthur Deshaies]]\n*Lucy Durand-Sikes\n*[[Leonard Edmondson]]\n*[[Fritz Eichenberg]]\n*Barbro Forslund\n*Sid Hammer\n*[[Shigeru Izumi]]\n*Lynda Kalman\n*[[Ruth Kerkovius]]\n*[[Po Kim|Po-Hyun Kim]]\n*Michael Knigin\n*[[Yasuhide Kobashi]]\n*[[Lee Krasner]]\n*[[Jacob Landau]]\n*[[Seong Moy]]\n*[[Carl E. Pickhardt Jr.|Carl Pickhardt]]\n*[[Steve Poleskie|Stephen Poleskie]]\n*[[Michael Ponce de Leon|Michael Ponce de Le\u00f3n]]\n*Clayton Pond\n*Walter Rogalski\n*[[Clare Romano]]\n*Andrew Stasik\n*[[Valerie Thornton]]\n*Vasilios Toulis\n*Ansei Uchima\n*Murray Zimiles\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*[https://www.nytimes.com/1964/01/05/archives/a-wee-plug-for-a-worthy-cause-all-about-the-pratt-graphic-art.html A Wee Plug for a Worth Cause; All About the Pratt Graphic Art Center And an Art Sale] by [[John Canaday]], New Yo